1
00:00:00,892 --> 00:00:27,658
Namo tatsa bhagavato hara-hatu samma-sambuddhasa Namo tatsa bhagavato hara-hatu samma-sambuddhasa Namo tatsa bhagavato hara-hatu samma-sambuddhasa

2
00:00:28,245 --> 00:00:34,176
homage to the Buddha, the blessed, noble, and fully self-enlightened one.

3
00:00:34,195 --> 00:00:47,939
So if you remember, we read the Kalama discourse, where the Buddha is basically saying that you have to question everything that's been taught to you, and it has to be true for yourself.

4
00:00:48,279 --> 00:00:50,622
You have to put it into practice and make sure it's true for yourself.

5
00:00:50,944 --> 00:00:54,168
Then, of course, he takes the opportunity of telling them what the Dharma is.

6
00:00:55,667 --> 00:01:04,620
But this here, this particular section is the Buddha actually telling people how to investigate whether the teacher is fully liberated or not.

7
00:01:04,641 --> 00:01:05,742
He was talking about himself.

8
00:01:07,123 --> 00:01:14,715
Thus have I heard on one occasion the Blessed One was living at Savatthi in Jeta's Grove and Adipindika's Park.

9
00:01:15,715 --> 00:01:17,477
And there he addressed the group of monks.

10
00:01:17,519 --> 00:01:24,308
Remember in the scriptures monks refers to the listeners so it could have been quite a large congregation really.

11
00:01:24,945 --> 00:01:27,349
Venerable Sir, they replied, and the Blessed One said this.

12
00:01:29,552 --> 00:01:43,353
A monk, occasionally I'll translate that as a person, a person who is an enquirer, not knowing how to gauge another's mind, should make an investigation of the Tathagata in order to find out whether or not he is perfectly enlightened.

13
00:01:44,275 --> 00:01:48,701
So he's already saying that to these people who are his followers.

14
00:01:49,221 --> 00:01:51,084
How do you know I'm the Tathagata?

15
00:01:51,725 --> 00:01:52,927
How do you know I'm fully liberated?

16
00:01:56,704 --> 00:02:03,492
And they reply, our teachings are rooted in the Blessed One, guided by the Blessed One, have the Blessed One as their resort.

17
00:02:03,591 --> 00:02:06,655
It would be good if the Blessed One would explain the meaning of these words.

18
00:02:07,176 --> 00:02:09,578
Having heard it from him, we shall remember it.

19
00:02:10,939 --> 00:02:13,262
Then listen and attend closely to what I shall say.

20
00:02:13,703 --> 00:02:14,522
Yes, Venerable Sir.

21
00:02:17,165 --> 00:02:23,893
A person who is an inquirer, not knowing how to gauge another's mind, in other words, not being able to see a person as they are,

22
00:02:24,751 --> 00:02:44,076
Should investigate the Tathagata, remember that's what he referred to himself as, he translates rather sillily as thus gone, just the transcendent I think, because he always talks about the other shore, so the transcendent one I think is the best translation I've come across.

23
00:02:44,097 --> 00:02:51,546
Should investigate the Tathagata with respect to two kinds of states, states cognizable through the eye and through the ear.

24
00:02:52,167 --> 00:02:52,647
Thus,

25
00:02:53,084 --> 00:03:01,073
Are there found in the Tathagata or not any defiled states cognizable through the eye or through the ear?

26
00:03:01,272 --> 00:03:03,975
In other words, how he behaves and what he says.

27
00:03:03,996 --> 00:03:12,745
And when he investigates him, he comes to know no defiled states cognizable through the eye or through the ear are found in the Tathagata.

28
00:03:13,286 --> 00:03:14,206
That's the first thing, right?

29
00:03:14,848 --> 00:03:18,872
So, in other words, observe a person's behavior and listen to what they say.

30
00:03:20,877 --> 00:03:23,621
When he comes to know this, he investigates further thus.

31
00:03:24,141 --> 00:03:30,770
Are there found in the Tathagata or not any mixed states cognizable through the eye or through the ear?

32
00:03:31,652 --> 00:03:39,122
When he investigates him thus, he knows no mixed states cognizable through the eye or through the ear are found in the Tathagata.

33
00:03:39,143 --> 00:03:45,812
So, mixed states refers to the fact that sometimes we behave well and sometimes we behave awfully.

34
00:03:46,152 --> 00:03:48,175
Sometimes we say things are good and sometimes not.

35
00:03:48,296 --> 00:03:49,298
So these are mixed states.

36
00:03:49,818 --> 00:03:51,620
But these are not found in the Tathagata.

37
00:03:51,639 --> 00:03:52,340
That's the important point.

38
00:03:55,122 --> 00:03:57,585
When he comes to know this, he investigates further.

39
00:03:57,604 --> 00:04:05,532
Are there found in the Tathagata or not cleansed states recognisable through the eye or through the ear?

40
00:04:05,633 --> 00:04:12,620
When he investigates this, cleansed states recognisable through the eye or through the ear are found in the Tathagata.

41
00:04:12,639 --> 00:04:14,581
And of course those are your beautiful states.

42
00:04:16,343 --> 00:04:17,985
There's a little story that...

43
00:04:18,269 --> 00:04:22,915
I remember hearing about Ajahn Chah, which if I remember rightly goes something like this.

44
00:04:24,016 --> 00:04:26,199
He'd heard that there was somebody who was fully liberated.

45
00:04:26,761 --> 00:04:29,103
And so he thought, well, I'll go and live with the person.

46
00:04:29,824 --> 00:04:38,677
And for a long time, I don't know how long, he was quite convinced that this person had in fact was fully liberated and he had that reputation.

47
00:04:39,418 --> 00:04:46,588
And one day he caught in, what had happened was somebody had offered meat to the monks there.

48
00:04:47,091 --> 00:04:57,283
and a dog had got onto the, had got onto the meat, and he saw this, the targeter, this very liberated person, get very angry and give the dog one hell of a kick.

49
00:04:59,105 --> 00:05:01,088
And upon that, it seems, he left.

50
00:05:03,290 --> 00:05:17,048
So, he doesn't say that, he doesn't say it's actually in this particular discourse, or at least he's not quoted in this discourse, that you have to live a long time with somebody to know what they're

51
00:05:20,673 --> 00:05:29,904
So that's the first thing, you see, to actually observe the person, the tāvaka, to see what they do and what they say.

52
00:05:29,944 --> 00:05:40,959
Now the next thing is, he investigates further, has this venerable one attained the wholesome state over a long time or did he attain it recently?

53
00:05:41,860 --> 00:05:49,649
When he investigates him, he comes to know the venerable one has attained this wholesome state over a long time and has not attained it just recently.

54
00:05:50,692 --> 00:05:54,196
So that gives a certain depth to his practice, you see.

55
00:05:56,418 --> 00:05:59,822
Now when it comes to know this, he investigates still further.

56
00:06:00,641 --> 00:06:08,829
Has the Venerable One acquired renown and attained fame so that the dangers connected with renown and fame are found in him?

57
00:06:10,471 --> 00:06:19,139
For as long as a monk has not acquired renown and attained fame, the dangers connected with renown and fame are not found in him.

58
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:20,480
But when he has acquired

59
00:06:20,882 --> 00:06:23,846
renowned and attained fame, those dangers are found in him.

60
00:06:24,206 --> 00:06:27,168
So the dangers are, of course, conceit, arrogance, etc.

61
00:06:28,370 --> 00:06:40,141
And when he investigates him, he knows thus, this venerable one has acquired renowned and attained fame, but the dangers associated with renowned fame are not found in him.

62
00:06:41,142 --> 00:06:45,047
That's another way you can tell whether somebody is fully liberated.

63
00:06:47,689 --> 00:06:50,232
And when he comes to know this, he investigates him further.

64
00:06:50,632 --> 00:06:57,038
Is the Venerable One restrained without fear, not restrained by fear?

65
00:06:57,978 --> 00:07:05,865
And does he avoid indulging in sensual pleasures because he is without lust through the destruction of lust?

66
00:07:05,886 --> 00:07:19,898
And when he investigates him, he comes to know, yes, the Venerable One is restrained without fear, not restrained by fear, and he avoids indulging in sensual pleasure because he is without lust through the destruction of lust.

67
00:07:20,502 --> 00:07:23,086
Lust here refers to any sensual pleasure.

68
00:07:26,050 --> 00:07:45,740
Now if others should ask that monk thus, what are the Venerable One's reasons and what is his evidence whereby he says that Venerable One is restrained without fear, not restrained by fear, and he avoids indulging in sensual pleasures because he is without lust through the destruction of lust.

69
00:07:45,761 --> 00:07:48,045
Answering rightly, that monk would answer thus,

70
00:07:48,834 --> 00:08:16,362
Whether that Venerable One dwells in the Sangha, or alone, while some there are well behaved, and some are ill behaved, and some there teach, and some there teach a group, while some here are seen concerned with material things, and some are sullied, are unsullied by material things, still the Venerable One does not despise anyone because of that.

71
00:08:17,675 --> 00:08:25,204
And I have heard and learned this from the Blessed One's lips, that I am restrained without fear, not constrained by fear.

72
00:08:25,824 --> 00:08:32,113
And I avoid indulging in sensual pleasure because I am without lust through the destruction of lust.

73
00:08:32,133 --> 00:08:40,383
In other words, even though he himself is fully liberated, he does not despise people who aren't because of their behaviour.

74
00:08:43,086 --> 00:08:44,727
He remains impartial, faithfully enough.

75
00:08:46,868 --> 00:08:50,893
So the Tathagata monk should be questioned further about this, about this.

76
00:08:51,673 --> 00:09:01,768
Are there found in the Tathagata or not any defiled statements cognizable through the eye or through the ear that the Tathagata would answer?

77
00:09:02,328 --> 00:09:08,356
No defiled states are cognizable through the eye or through the ear are found in the Tathagata.

78
00:09:09,398 --> 00:09:16,807
And if asked, are there found in the Tathagata or not any mixed states cognizable through the eye or through the ear that the Tathagata would answer thus?

79
00:09:17,107 --> 00:09:21,293
Gnomic states cognizable through the eye or through the ear are found in the Tathagata.

80
00:09:22,354 --> 00:09:36,431
And if asked are they found in the Tathagata or not, cleansed states cognizable through eye or through the ear, the Tathagata would say, cleansed states cognizable through the eye or through the ear are found in the Tathagata.

81
00:09:36,750 --> 00:09:42,738
They are my pathway, my domain, yet I do not identify with them.

82
00:09:43,458 --> 00:09:45,782
So now he's answered these questions, you see.

83
00:09:46,133 --> 00:09:51,481
but he makes the clear statement that this is the way he lives, but he does not identify with them.

84
00:09:52,744 --> 00:09:56,330
So again it's a statement of the target being the transcendent one.

85
00:09:57,130 --> 00:10:00,355
Transcendent but also imminent in the world.

86
00:10:04,423 --> 00:10:09,892
A disciple should approach the teacher who speaks thus in order to hear the Dharma.

87
00:10:09,951 --> 00:10:10,452
The

88
00:10:10,822 --> 00:10:18,269
teaches him the Dhamma with its successively higher levels, with its successively more sublime levels, with its dark and bright counterparts.

89
00:10:19,090 --> 00:10:29,480
And as the teacher teaches the Dhamma to a monk in this way, through direct knowledge of a certain teaching here in that Dhamma, the monk comes to a conclusion about the teachings.

90
00:10:30,361 --> 00:10:37,369
He places confidence in the Buddha thus, the Blessed One is perfectly enlightened, the Dhamma is well proclaimed by the Blessed One,

91
00:10:37,567 --> 00:10:39,610
and the Sangha is practicing in a good way.

92
00:10:39,951 --> 00:10:50,847
So here we see the growth of faith, and the growth of faith drawing the monk, or the practitioner, into further practice.

93
00:10:55,014 --> 00:10:58,479
There's a note here which sort of tries to clarify that.

94
00:10:58,619 --> 00:10:59,500
I may as well try and read it.

95
00:11:00,442 --> 00:11:06,410
When the Dharma has been taught by the Master, this is from one of the commentaries, when the Dharma has been taught by the Master,

96
00:11:07,318 --> 00:11:22,000
the monk, by directly knowing the Dharma, through penetration of the path, fruit and Nibbana, comes to a conclusion regarding the preliminary teachings of the Dharma about the aids of enlightenment, which are the factors of enlightenment.

97
00:11:22,020 --> 00:11:26,466
In other words, it's a long-winded way of saying that.

98
00:11:26,727 --> 00:11:34,980
As the person becomes, has his own experience of path and fruit, he understands the factors of enlightenment.

99
00:11:43,297 --> 00:11:56,171
And then finally, what are the Venerable One's reasons and what is his evidence whereby he says the Blessed One is perfectly enlightened, the Dharma is well proclaimed by the Blessed One, the Sangha is practising the good way.

100
00:11:56,191 --> 00:12:02,116
Answering rightly, that monk would answer thus, Here friends, I approach the Blessed One in order to hear the Dharma.

101
00:12:02,136 --> 00:12:09,625
The Blessed One taught me the Dharma with its successively high levels, with its successively more sublime levels, with its dark and bright counterpart.

102
00:12:10,380 --> 00:12:23,477
And as the Blessed One taught the Dhamma in me in this way, through direct knowledge of a certain teaching here in that Dhamma, I came to the conclusion that the teachings, about the teachings, and I placed confidence in the teacher thus.

103
00:12:23,958 --> 00:12:32,110
So in other words, at this point he's actually had the experience of path and fruit, and the confidence is a strong one in the Buddha.

104
00:12:33,191 --> 00:12:39,139
The Blessed One is perfectly enlightened, the Dhamma is well proclaimed by the Blessed One, and the Sangha is practicing well.

105
00:12:40,485 --> 00:12:55,640
When anyone's faith has been planted, rooted and established in the Tathagata through these reasons, terms and phrases, his faith is said to be supported by reasons, rooted in the vision, in other words his own experience, firm.

106
00:12:56,422 --> 00:13:04,229
It is invincible by any ascetic or Brahmin or Deva or Mara or Brahma or by anyone in the world.

107
00:13:05,671 --> 00:13:10,154
That is how monks, there is an investigation of the Dhamma in accordance with the Dhamma

108
00:13:10,777 --> 00:13:16,148
And that is how the Tathagata is well investigated in accordance with the Dhamma.

109
00:13:16,168 --> 00:13:25,947
That is what the Blessed One said and the monks were satisfied, the listeners were satisfied and delighted in the Buddha's words.

110
00:13:25,966 --> 00:13:30,134
So, the Buddha here is telling us that

111
00:13:33,472 --> 00:13:36,857
We just need to keep that questioning going.

112
00:13:36,878 --> 00:13:41,943
We need not to take anything by just because he's the Buddha.

113
00:13:43,285 --> 00:13:49,354
Everything that has been handed down to us has to be verified by our own personal experience.

114
00:13:49,494 --> 00:13:51,716
That's what it comes down to.

115
00:13:51,736 --> 00:14:01,269
I can only hope this small exposition has been of some assistance and that you may be fully liberated from all suffering sooner rather than later.

116
00:14:03,341 --> 00:14:05,639
solitude, solitude.

